<item>
            <title>[SOLR-16978] Many APIs now only allow lowercase boolean values</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-16978</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Many APIs (at least all the ones I checked) now only allow lowercase &lt;tt&gt;true&lt;/tt&gt; and &lt;tt&gt;false&lt;/tt&gt; for boolean values, if &lt;tt&gt;True&lt;/tt&gt; or &lt;tt&gt;False&lt;/tt&gt; are used (or any other case variation) it will result in:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;tt&gt;invalid boolean value: False&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This was allowed in previous versions of Solr&lt;/p&gt;</description>
